name: Cars-Axile
description: An axle is a rod or shaft that connects a pair of wheels to propel them and preserve the position of the wheels to one another. In a car, the engine applies the pressure to the axle which rotates the wheels and strikes the automobile forward. In different words, axles deliver the using strength from the engine to the wheels.

name: Cars-Bracking

name: Cars-Chassis

name: Cars-Clutch

name: Cars-Differential

name: Cars-Engine

name: Cars-Gearings

name: Cars-Steering
